The paper proposes a process for dispatching the operation of a distribution feeder using a battery energy storage system (BESS) and model predictive control (MPC). This involves data-driven forecasting and real-time operation, which suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY). The use of forecasting and MPC also involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a monitoring infrastructure, which could relate to embedded systems (cs.ET) or software engineering (cs.SE).
